{"type":"message","id":"3ae953e9","parentId":"d75229f2","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:09:26.249Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So Son has:\n1. `stench_number_function.md` - the function definition file that Spirit created and synced over\n2. `generate.py` - an actual Python script that implements the algorithm\n3. `verify.py` - a verification script\n4. `stench_number.db` - the database\n\nSon actually wrote real code for this! Let me check what generate.py looks like, so I can tell 汀桑 where the algorithm lives.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_MRlOhVDwaG7cW3YU9EGA5596","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"~/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py"},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"~/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":433,"output":153,"cacheRead":44288,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":94,"totalTokens":44874,"cost":{"input":0.000060620000000000006,"output":0.00004284,"cacheRead":0.001240064,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001343524}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780247363880,"responseId":"11e91276-a150-4964-9af0-8b13ffc3d60d"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b6d8170b","parentId":"3ae953e9","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:09:27.008Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_MRlOhVDwaG7cW3YU9EGA5596","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Generate stench number expressions for a given target number.\"\"\"\nimport json\nimport math\nimport random\n\nN = 20070521\n\n# Base number set\nbase_nums = [1, 4, 5, 11, 14, 15, 51, 54]\nextended_nums = [114, 514, 1145, 1451, 14514, 114514, 1145140]\nall_nums = sorted(set(base_nums + extended_nums), reverse=True)\n\ndef find_decomp(target, max_terms=8):\n    \"\"\"Try to decompose target as sum/difference of base/extended numbers.\"\"\"\n    # Greedy approach\n    terms = []\n    remaining = target\n    for _ in range(max_terms):\n        if remaining == 0:\n            break\n        # Find nearest number\n        best = min(all_nums, key=lambda x: abs(x - remaining) if x <= remaining * 1.5 else abs(remaining))\n        if remaining > 0 and abs(remaining - best) < abs(best - remaining):\n            terms.append(('+', best))\n            remaining -= best\n        elif remaining > 0:\n            terms.append(('+', best))\n            remaining -= best\n        elif remaining < 0:\n            terms.append(('-', best))\n            remaining += best\n        else:\n            break\n    return terms\n\n# Approach 1: 114514 × 175 + 514 × 59 + 5 × 54 - 5 × 5\nexpr1_parts = []\n# 175 = 114 + 54 + 5 + 1 + 1\n# 59 = 54 + 5\nexpr1 = f\"114514 × (114 + 54 + 5 + 1 + 1) + 514 × (54 + 5) + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\"\n\n# Approach 2: Different decomposition\n# Try 114514 × 176 - 514 × 4 + something\n# 114514 × 176 = 114514 × 200 - 114514 × 24\n# = 22902800 - 2748336 = 20154464\n# 20154464 - 20070521 = 83943... too much\n\n# Try: 114514 × 170 + something\n# 114514 × 170 = 114514 × 100 + 114514 × 70 = 11451400 + 8015980 = 19467380\n# 20070521 - 19467380 = 603141\n# 603141 = 114514 × 5 + 30571 = 572570 + 30571... same thing basically\n\n# Try: 1145140 × 17 + 114514 × 5 + ...\n# 1145140 × 17 = 19467380\n# 114514 × 5 = 572570\n# Sum = 20039950\n# remaining = 30571\n# 30571 = 514 × 59 + 245 = 514 × (54+5) + 5 × 54 - 5 × 5\n\nexpr2_a = \"1145140 × 17 + 114514 × 5 + 514 × (54 + 5) + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\"\n\n# Check: 1145140 × 17 = 19467380\n# 114514 × 5 = 572570\n# 19467380 + 572570 = 20039950\n# 514 × 54 = 27756\n# 514 × 5 = 2570\n# 27756 + 2570 = 30326\n# 5 × 54 = 270\n# 5 × 5 = 25\n# 30326 + 270 - 25 = 30571\n# 20039950 + 30571 = 20070521 ✓\n\n# Approach 3: Use 14 as multiplier\n# 20070521 / 14 = 1433608.6...\n# 14 × 1433608 = 20070512\n# 20070521 - 20070512 = 9\n# 20070521 = 14 × 1433608 + 9\n# 1433608 = ?\n\n# Let me try algebraic: N = a × b + c where a,b,c are stench numbers\n# Try with mixed ops\n\n# Approach 3: 20070521 = 114514 × 175 + 514 × 59 + 245 (where 245 = 5 × 49 = 5 × (54-5))\nexpr3 = f\"114514 × (54 + 54 + 54 + 11 + 1 + 1) + 514 × (54 + 5) + (54 − 5) × 5\"\n\n# Actually let me compute 114514 × 175 differently:\n# 114514 × 175 = 114514 × (200 - 25) = 22902800 - 2862850 = 20039950\n# 175 = 200 - 25 = 200 - 25\n# 200 = 5 × 5 × 4 × 2... not great\n\n# Let me just use 114514 × 175 = 114514 × (114 + 54 + 5 + 1 + 1)\n# and format differently\n\n# Approach 4: Multiplication heavy\n# Check if 20070521 = a × b + c where a is a stench number\nfor a in [114514, 14514, 1145, 514, 114]:\n    q = N // a\n    r = N % a\n    print(f\"{N} = {a} × {q} + {r}\")\n\n# Approach 4: Let me think about pure sum decomposition\n# 20070521 = 11451400 + 8619121\n# 8619121 = 1145140 × 7 + 514 × 514 + ...\n# 1145140 × 7 = 8015980\n# 8619121 - 8015980 = 603141\n# 603141 = 114514 × 5 + 30571 = 572570 + 30571\n# 30571 = 514 × 59 + 245 = 514 × (54+5) + 5 × 49\n# 49 = 54 - 5\n# So: 20070521 = 11451400 + 1145140 × 7 + 114514 × 5 + 514 × (54+5) + 5 × (54 - 5)\n\nexpr4 = f\"114514 × 100 + 114514 × 70 + 114514 × 5 + 514 × 54 + 514 × 5 + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\"\n# Check: 114514×100 + 114514×70 + 114514×5 = 114514×175 = 20039950 ✓\n# 514×54 + 514×5 = 514×59 = 30326 ✓\n# 5×54 - 5×5 = 245 ✓\n# Total: 20039950 + 30326 + 245 = 20070521 ✓\n\n# Approach 5: Use 14514\n# 14514 × 1382 + 12173 (we computed earlier)\n# Let me try: 14514 × (1145 + 114 + 114 + 5 + 4) + ...\n# 14514 × 1145 = 16618530\n# 14514 × 114 = 1654596\n# 14514 × 114 = 1654596\n# 14514 × 5 = 72570\n# 14514 × 4 = 58056\n# Sum = 16618530 + 1654596 = 18273126\n# 18273126 + 1654596 = 19927722\n# 19927722 + 72570 = 20000292\n# 20000292 + 58056 = 20058348\n# Remaining: 20070521 - 20058348 = 12173\n\n# 12173 = 114514 / 10 + ... no\n# 12173 = 114 × 106 + ...\n# 114 × 106 = 12084\n# 12173 - 12084 = 89\n# 89 = 54 + 15 + 15 + 5\n\n# This is getting too complex. Let me use the simpler expressions.\n\nprint()\nprint(\"=== GENERATED EXPRESSIONS ===\")\nprint(f\"\\n📿 最佳恶臭：\")\nprint(f\"{N} = 114514 × 175 + 514 × 59 + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\")\nprint(f\"     = 114514 × (114 + 54 + 5 + 1 + 1) + 514 × (54 + 5) + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n💩 其他恶臭组合2：\")\nprint(f\"{N} = 1145140 × 17 + 114514 × 5 + 514 × (54 + 5) + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n💩 其他恶臭组合3：\")\nprint(f\"{N} = 114514 × 100 + 114514 × 70 + 114514 × 5 + 514 × 54 + 514 × 5 + 5 × 54 − 5 × 5\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n💩 其他恶臭组合4：\")\nprint(f\"{N} = (114 + 54 + 5 + 1 + 1) × 114514 + (54 + 5) × 514 + (54 − 5) × 5\")\n\n# Let me also try a different strategy: N = 514 × 39047 + 363\nprint(f\"\\n💩 其他恶臭组合5：\")\nprint(f\"{N} = 514 × 39047 + 114 + 114 + 114 + 14 + 5 + 1 + 1\")\n\n# Or even simpler approach:\n# Check modulo\nprint(f\"\\n--- Alternative checks ---\")\nfor n in [114514, 14514, 1145, 514, 114]:\n    print(f\"  {N} ÷ {n} = {N // n} rem {N % n}\")\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780247367008}}
