{"type":"message","id":"974af14c","parentId":"e6e4dd1f","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:31:13.981Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_ET_5uUgna0ZIh5Btb9WVegx2319","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\n    \"\"\"递归恶臭拆解：用114514反复取模拆分，直到每个部分都小于114514可直拆\"\"\"\n    if depth > 3:\n        return str(n)\n    if n < 114514:\n        # 小数字尝试用DFS拆\n        if n in ALL_POOL or n < 20:\n            return str(n)\n        # 用 514/114 拆一层\n        for divisor in [514, 114, 14514]:\n            if n > divisor:\n                k = n // divisor\n                r = n % divisor\n                if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n                    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n                    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n                    return f\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k = n // 114514\n    r = n % 114514\n    \n    if r == 0 or has_digit_zero(r):\n        # 余数有0，换个拆法\n        k = n // 514\n        r = n % 514\n        if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n            k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n            r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n            return f\"514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n    return f\"114514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n\n\ndef generate_academic(target):\n    \"\"\"学院派兜底：递归用114514反复取模拆解大数\"\"\"\n    results_lines = []\n    results_lines.append(f\"🤢 数字 {target} 的恶臭拆解（学院派）：\")\n    results_lines.append(\"\")\n\n    expr = _recurse_stench(target)\n\n[36 more lines in file. Use offset=946 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780248673980}}
{"type":"message","id":"5bea9c88","parentId":"974af14c","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:31:28.332Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear:\n\n1. `if n in ALL_POOL or n < 20: return str(n)` - this stops too early. `n in ALL_POOL` is fine (those are true stench numbers), but `n < 20` just returns the number as-is without trying to decompose it.\n\n2. For the divisor approach, it tries 514, 114, 14514 but these are bigger than many numbers. For numbers like 87, none of the divisors will work since 87 < 114, so it falls through to `return str(n)`.\n\n3. The `depth > 3` limit also prevents deep recursion.\n\nThe fix:\n- Remove `n < 20` shortcut - only stop at BASE_POOL + EXT_POOL + MEGA_POOL\n- For numbers not in the pool, always try to decompose using any smaller number from the pool\n- Use addition decomposition: n = a + b where a and b are from the pool (or recursively decomposed)\n- Increase depth limit or remove it\n\nLet me think about the right approach:\n\nFor any n that's not in BASE_POOL or EXT_POOL:\n1. Find the largest number from ALL_POOL that's <= n (let's call it a)\n2. Decompose n = a + (n - a) recursively\n3. Or find the smallest number from ALL_POOL that's >= n, decompose as a - (a - n)\n\nBut this could lead to deep recursion. A simpler approach:\n1. Find the closest ALL_POOL number <= n, call it a\n2. n = a + (n-a) where n-a is recursively decomposed\n3. Or if a > n, use n = (a) - (a-n)\n\nActually, the simplest approach: for any n not in the pool, greedily subtract the largest pool number that's <= n:\n- 87 → find largest pool <= 87 = 54 (or 51 or 54)\n- 87 = 54 + 33\n- 33 → largest pool <= 33 = 15 (or 14 or 15)\n- 33 = 15 + 15 + 3... hmm 3 is not in pool\n- 33 = 15 + 11 + 5 + 1 + 1... that works\n\nOr: \n- 87 = 54 + 15 + 11 + 5 + 1 + 1 = 54 + 15 + 11 + 5 + 1 + 1\n\nLet me rewrite _recurse_stench to decompose until all parts are in BASE_POOL ∪ EXT_POOL.\n\nActually, let me define a \"pure\" set: numbers that are allowed in the final expression. This should include:\n- BASE_POOL: [1, 4, 5, 11, 14, 15, 51, 54]\n- EXT_POOL: [114, 514, 1145, 1451, 14514, 114514]\n- MEGA_POOL: [1145140, 1919810, 1145141919810]\n\nAnd any number not in this set must be decomposed further.\n\nFor decomposition, use subtraction of the nearest lower pool number.\n\nLet me rewrite the function.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_E9leQvFzJmwuFfVV32I36732","name":"edit","arguments":{"newText":"def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\n    \"\"\"递归恶臭拆解：一直拆到所有数字都在恶臭数字池中\"\"\"\n    if depth > 5:\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 已在池中 → 直接返回\n    if n in ALL_POOL_MEGA:\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 小数字但不在池中 → 用加法拆成池中数字之和\n    if n < 114514:\n        # 贪心：从大到小用池中数字凑\n        pool_sorted = sorted(ALL_POOL, reverse=True)\n        parts = []\n        remaining = n\n        for p in pool_sorted:\n            while remaining >= p:\n                parts.append(str(p))\n                remaining -= p\n            if remaining == 0:\n                break\n        if remaining == 0 and len(parts) >= 2:\n            return \" + \".join(parts)\n        # 减法方案：用稍大的池中数字减\n        for p in pool_sorted:\n            if p > n:\n                diff = p - n\n                if diff in ALL_POOL:\n                    return f\"{p} − {diff}\"\n                diff_parts = []\n                r2 = diff\n                for p2 in pool_sorted:\n                    while r2 >= p2:\n                        diff_parts.append(str(p2))\n                        r2 -= p2\n                    if r2 == 0:\n                        break\n                if r2 == 0 and len(diff_parts) >= 1:\n                    return f\"{p} − {' + '.join(diff_parts)}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 大数：用114514取模拆\n    k = n // 114514\n    r = n % 114514\n    \n    if r == 0 or has_digit_zero(r):\n        # 余数有0，换514\n        k = n // 514\n        r = n % 514\n        if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n            k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n            r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n            return f\"514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        # 再换114\n        k = n // 114\n        r = n % 114\n        if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n            k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n            r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n            return f\"114 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n    return f\"114514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"","path":"~/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py","edits":[{"oldText":"def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\n    \"\"\"递归恶臭拆解：用114514反复取模拆分，直到每个部分都小于114514可直拆\"\"\"\n    if depth > 3:\n        return str(n)\n    if n < 114514:\n        # 小数字尝试用DFS拆\n        if n in ALL_POOL or n < 20:\n            return str(n)\n        # 用 514/114 拆一层\n        for divisor in [514, 114, 14514]:\n            if n > divisor:\n                k = n // divisor\n                r = n % divisor\n                if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n                    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n                    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n                    return f\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k = n // 114514\n    r = n % 114514\n    \n    if r == 0 or has_digit_zero(r):\n        # 余数有0，换个拆法\n        k = n // 514\n        r = n % 514\n        if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n            k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n            r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n            return f\"514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n    return f\"114514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\""}]},"partialArgs":"{\"newText\": \"def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"递归恶臭拆解：一直拆到所有数字都在恶臭数字池中\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    if depth > 5:\\n        return str(n)\\n    \\n 