{"type":"message","id":"57139630","parentId":"bdb0f93a","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:32:15.970Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The output is way too long now - it's using greedy addition which generates `1451 + 1451 + 1451 ...` many times. The greedy approach just adds the same number over and over.\n\nThere are two issues:\n1. The expression is too long and ugly (but it IS pure - only 114514 series numbers)\n2. It should use multiplication to shorten: e.g., `14514 × N` instead of `14514 + 14514 + ...`\n\nBut for small remainders, the greedy addition is OK if the numbers are small. For a big remainder like this, we need a different approach.\n\nActually let me think about what happened:\n- 1145141919810 / 114514 = 10000229, remainder 0\n- Wait no, let me check: k = 10000229, r = ?\n\nHmm, actually the function decomposes as:\n- n = 114514 × k + r where k = 114514 × 54 + ...\n- k itself is 114514 × 54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1 + ...\n\nWait, that doesn't look right. Let me trace:\n- 1145141919810 / 114514 = 10000229... hmm that doesn't make sense.\n\nLet me actually compute: 114514 × 10000000 = 1,145,140,000,000\n1145141919810 - 1,145,140,000,000 = 191,919,810\n191,919,810 / 114514 = 1675 point something\n1675 × 114514 = 191,810,950\n191,919,810 - 191,810,950 = 108,860\n\nHmm, that's complicated. Let me just check: does the function work correctly for smaller numbers?\n\nLet me test 87 first.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"太长了，全是加法凑的。小数字用贪心加法没问题，但大数字的余数这么拆太啰嗦了。让我换个更聪明的拆法——对余数也尝试乘法拆分。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_rwIRN9SGKj6LIRg99hg02900","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number && python3 generate.py 87 2>&1 && echo \"========\" && python3 generate.py 20070521 2>&1 | head -10","timeout":15},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number && python3 generate.py 87 2>&1 && echo \\\"========\\\" && python3 generate.py 20070521 2>&