{"type":"message","id":"44ee62ef","parentId":"57139630","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:32:23.468Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_00_rwIRN9SGKj6LIRg99hg02900","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🤢 数字 87 的恶臭拆解（学院派）：\n\n📿 最佳恶臭（学院派）：\n87 = 54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1\n恶臭等级：3/10 💨 微微发臭\n\n--- \n🫵 你也是恶臭人了！\n========\n🤢 数字 20070521 的恶臭拆解：\n\n📿 最佳恶臭：\n20070521 = (514 × 546665) ÷ 14 + 54 + 51 + 1\n恶臭等级：5/10 🤢 有点味道了\n\n💩 其他恶臭组合：\n20070521 = (114 × 1936627) ÷ 11 + 15 + 4 + 4\n20070521 = (114 × 2464798) ÷ 14 + 15 + 4 + 4\n20070521 = 14514 × 1382 + 12173"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":6083,"aggregated":"🤢 数字 87 的恶臭拆解（学院派）：\n\n📿 最佳恶臭（学院派）：\n87 = 54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1\n恶臭等级：3/10 💨 微微发臭\n\n--- \n🫵 你也是恶臭人了！\n========\n🤢 数字 20070521 的恶臭拆解：\n\n📿 最佳恶臭：\n20070521 = (514 × 546665) ÷ 14 + 54 + 51 + 1\n恶臭等级：5/10 🤢 有点味道了\n\n💩 其他恶臭组合：\n20070521 = (114 × 1936627) ÷ 11 + 15 + 4 + 4\n20070521 = (114 × 2464798) ÷ 14 + 15 + 4 + 4\n20070521 = 14514 × 1382 + 12173","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780248743466}}
{"type":"message","id":"213f0306","parentId":"44ee62ef","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:32:33.131Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, 87 now correctly decomposes to `54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1` - all in the pool. Pure! But it's 3/10 only because it uses +. \n\nFor 1145141919810, the issue is that the greedy addition for the remainder produces a very long expression. But the numbers ARE pure - all in the 114514 series.\n\nThe problem is: the function only uses addition for small numbers, and for the k part of big numbers, it just recurses. The remainder r = 1145141919810 % 114514 is being decomposed using greedy addition, producing a long string of + 14514 + 14514 + ...\n\nActually let me check: what is 1145141919810 // 114514 and 1145141919810 % 114514?\n\n114514 * 10000000 = 11,451,400,000,000? No that's way too big.\n114514 * 1000000 = 114,514,000,000\n1145141919810 ≈ 1.145e12\n114514 ≈ 1.145e5\n1.145e12 / 1.145e5 = 1.0e7 = 10,000,000\n\nSo k ≈ 10,000,000 and r ≈ something.\n\nLet me check: 114514 * 9999999 = ?\n114514 * 10000000 = 1,145,140,000,000 (this is 1.14514e12)\n1145141919810 - 1,145,140,000,000 = 191,9810? \n\nWait: 1145141919810 - 1145140000000 = 1919810\n\nYes! So 1145141919810 = 114514 * 10000000 + 1919810\n\n10000000 = ?\nk = 10000000\n\n10000000 / 114514 ≈ 87.3 \n114514 * 87 = 9,962,718\n10000000 - 9,962,718 = 37,282\n\nSo k = 114514 × 87 + 37282\n\nBut 87 needs to be decomposed: 87 = 54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1\nAnd 37282 needs decomposition too.\n\nr = 1919810 - this is in MEGA_POOL? Let me check: MEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810, 1145141919810]\n\nYes! 1919810 is in MEGA_POOL. But I changed the check to ALL_POOL, so it won't be treated as \"pure\" anymore. Let me check: 1919810 % 114514 = ?\n\n114514 * 16 = 1,832,224\n1919810 - 1,832,224 = 87,586 = 114514 * 0.76... \n\nHmm, 1919810 just is a stench number (from the original 1145141919810 meme). It shouldn't be decomposed further.\n\nWait, the problem is that 1919810 IS in MEGA_POOL but it's also a valid \"atomic\" stench number. The issue was that 1145141919810 itself was also in MEGA_POOL which prevented decomposition.\n\nLet me reconsider: I should remove 1145141919810 from MEGA_POOL but keep 1919810 in it, because 1919810 is an atomic stench sub-number but 1145141919810 is a composite.\n\nActually, let me just handle this differently. In the _recurse_stench function, instead of checking `n in ALL_POOL`, I should check if n is in ALL_POOL_MEGA except for 1145141919810 specifically. Or better: just remove 1145141919810 from MEGA_POOL entirely.\n\nMEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810]  - remove 1145141919810","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_6Es1XomPoqlo0BwRmuzI5019","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Remove 1145141919810 from MEGA_POOL since it should be decomposable\ncontent = content.replace(\n    'MEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810, 1145141919810]',\n    'MEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810]'\n)\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint('done')\n\"\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'r') as f:\\n    content = f.read()\\n\\n# Remove 1145141919810 from MEGA_POOL since it should be decomposable\\ncontent = content.replace(\\n    'MEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810, 1145141919810]',\\n    'MEGA_POOL = [1145140, 1919810]'\\n)\\n\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'w') as f:\\n    f.write(content)\\nprint('done')\\n\\\"\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":303,"output":1044,"cacheRead":99328,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":858,"totalTokens":100675,"cost":{"input":0.000042420000000000004,"output":0.00029232,"cacheRead":0.002781184,"ca