{"type":"message","id":"d7f96377","parentId":"ac58572c","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:33:03.676Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it still degenerates into a long addition chain for the remainder of 10000000. Let me check: what is 10000000 decomposed as?\n\n10000000 / 114514 = 87.3...\n114514 * 87 = 9,962,718\n10000000 - 9,962,718 = 37,282\n\nSo k = 114514 * 87 + 37282\n\n87 = 54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1 (pure! all in pool)\n37282 = ?\n\n37282 / 14514 = 2.56...\n14514 * 2 = 29,028\n37282 - 29,028 = 8,254\n\n8,254 = ?\n\nThis is getting very long because the remainder 8254 gets decomposed by greedy addition:\n8254 = 1451 + 1451 + 1451 + 1451 + 1451 + 514 + 114 + 114 + 114 + 114 + 15 + 14\n\nThat's 12 terms for 8254 alone.\n\nThe greedy addition approach produces pure expressions but they're very long. The real issue is that for numbers like 8254, the greedy approach from ALL_POOL [1,4,5,11,14,15,51,54,114,514,1145,1451,14514,114514] uses 1451 which is the largest number <= 8254, then repeats it 5 times.\n\nA better approach: for numbers not in the pool, try multiplication first. 8254 = 514 × 16 + ... or 114 × 72 + ...\n\nActually, the base _recurse_stench already tried this with divisors [514, 114, 14514] in the original version. But I removed that for small numbers and replaced it with greedy addition.\n\nLet me combine both approaches: for small numbers, try divisor-based decomposition first, then fall back to addition.\n\nActually, wait - the current version for n < 114514 only does addition/subtraction. It doesn't try multiplication at all. I need to add that back.\n\nLet me rewrite _recurse_stench again, but this time combine multiplication decomposition for small numbers AND addition fallback.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"还太长。小数字只做了加法没试乘法拆分。让我把乘法和加法都加上。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_StNfrEt49qNMFUDaiURn7339","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold_func_start = 'def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):'\n# Find the function\nimport re\nstart = content.index(old_func_start)\n# Find where it ends (next def or end of section)\n# The function ends at the blank line before 'def generate_academic'\nend = content.index('def generate_academic')\n# Find the blank line before generate_academic\n# Go backward from end to find the last blank line\nfunc_text = content[start:end].rstrip()\n# Find the indentation level\n\nnew_func = '''def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"递归恶臭拆解：一直拆到所有数字都在恶臭数字池中\\\"\\\"\\\"\n    if depth > 6:\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 特殊处理 1145141919810\n    if n == 1145141919810:\n        k_part = _recurse_stench(10000000, depth+1)\n        return f\\\"114514 × {k_part} + 1919810\\\"\n    \n    # 已在池中 → 直接返回\n    if n in ALL_POOL_MEGA:\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 用乘法拆分小数字\n    if n < 114514:\n        pool_sorted = sorted(ALL_POOL, reverse=True)\n        # 方案1：用池中除数拆\n        for divisor in [14514, 514, 114, 1451, 1145, 54, 51]:\n            if n > divisor:\n                k = n // divisor\n                r = n % divisor\n                if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n                    if (k in ALL_POOL or k < 114514) and (r in ALL_POOL or r < 114514):\n                        k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n                        r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n                        return f\\\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"\n        \n        # 方案2：贪心加法（从大到小凑）\n        parts = []\n        remaining = n\n        for p in pool_sorted:\n            while remaining >= p:\n                parts.append(str(p))\n                remaining -= p\n            if remaining == 0:\n                break\n        if remaining == 0 and len(parts) >= 2:\n            return ' + '.join(parts)\n        \n        # 方案3：减法\n        for p in pool_sorted:\n            if p > n:\n                diff = p - n\n                if diff in ALL_POOL:\n                    return f\\\"{p} − {diff}\\\"\n                diff_parts = []\n                r2 = diff\n                for p2 in pool_sorted:\n                    while r2 >= p2:\n                        diff_parts.append(str(p2))\n                        r2 -= p2\n                    if r2 == 0:\n                        break\n                if r2 == 0 and len(diff_parts) >= 1:\n                    return f\\\"{p} − {' + '.join(diff_parts)}\\\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    # 大数：用114514取模拆\n    k = n // 114514\n    r = n % 114514\n    \n    if r == 0 or has_digit_zero(r):\n        for divisor, name in [(514, '514'), (114, '114'), (14514, '14514')]:\n            k = n // divisor\n            r = n % divisor\n            if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\n                k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n                r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n                return f\\\"{name} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"\n        return str(n)\n    \n    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\n    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\n    return f\\\"114514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"'''\n\n# Replace everything from def _recurse_stench to def generate_academic\ncontent = content[:start] + new_func + '\\\\n\\\\n' + content[end:]\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint('done')\n\"\n"},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'r') as f:\\n    content = f.read()\\n\\nold_func_start = 'def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):'\\n# Find the function\\nimport re\\nstart = content.index(old_func_start)\\n# Find where it ends (next def or end of section)\\n# The function ends at the blank line before 'def generate_academic'\\nend = content.index('def generate_academic')\\n# Find the blank line before generate_academic\\n# Go backward from end to find the last blank line\\nfunc_text = content[start:end].rstrip()\\n# Find the indentation level\\n\\nnew_func = '''def _recurse_stench(n, depth=0):\\n    \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"递归恶臭拆解：一直拆到所有数字都在恶臭数字池中\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\n    if depth > 6:\\n        return str(n)\\n    \\n    # 特殊处理 1145141919810\\n    if n == 1145141919810:\\n        k_part = _recurse_stench(10000000, depth+1)\\n        return f\\\\\\\"114514 × {k_part} + 1919810\\\\\\\"\\n    \\n    # 已在池中 → 直接返回\\n    if n in ALL_POOL_MEGA:\\n        return str(n)\\n    \\n    # 用乘法拆分小数字\\n    if n < 114514:\\n        pool_sorted = sorted(ALL_POOL, reverse=True)\\n        # 方案1：用池中除数拆\\n        for divisor in [14514, 514, 114, 1451, 1145, 54, 51]:\\n            if n > divisor:\\n                k = n // divisor\\n                r = n % divisor\\n                if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                    if (k in ALL_POOL or k < 114514) and (r in ALL_POOL or r < 114514):\\n                        k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                        r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                        return f\\\\\\\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\\\\\"\\n        \\n        # 方案2：贪心加法（从大到小凑）\\n        parts = []\\n        remaining = n\\n        for p in pool_sorted:\\n            while remaining >= p:\\n                parts.append(str(p))\\n                remaining -= p\\n            if remaining == 0:\\n                break\\n        if remaining == 0 and len(parts) >= 2:\\n            return ' + '.join(parts)\\n        \\n        # 方案3：减法\\n        for p in pool_sorted:\\n            if p > n:\\n                diff = p - n\\n                if diff in ALL_POOL:\\n                    return f\\\\\\\"{p} − {diff}\\\\\\\"\\n                diff_parts = []\\n                r2 = diff\\n                for p2 in pool_sorted:\\n                    while r2 >= p2:\\n                        diff_parts.append(str(p2))\\n                        r2 -= p2\\n                    if r2 == 0:\\n                        break\\n                if r2 == 0 and len(diff_parts) >= 1:\\n                    return f\\\\\\\"{p} − {' + '.join(diff_parts)}\\\\\\\"\\n        return str(n)\\n    \\n    # 大数：用114514取模拆\\n    k = n // 114514\\n    r = n % 114514\\n    \\n    if r == 0 or has_digit_zero(r):\\n        for divisor, name in [(514, '514'), (114, '114'), (14514, '14514')]:\\n            k = n // divisor\\n            r = n % divisor\\n            if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                return f\\\\\\\"{name} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\\\\\"\\n        return str(n)\\n    \\n    k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n    r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n    return f\\\\\\\"114514 × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\\\\\"'''\\n\\n# Replace everything from def _recurse_stench to def generate_academic\\ncontent = content[:start] + new_func + '\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n' + content[end:]\\n\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'w') as f:\\n    f.write(content)\\nprint('done')\\n\\\"\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":284,"output":1532,"cacheRead":101120,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":479,"totalTokens":102936,"cost":{"input":0.000039760000000000006,"output":0.00042896000000000004,"cacheRead":0.0028313599999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00330008}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780248771822,"responseId":"89f3bce9-ff42-4e59-ac2b-27843543636f"}}
