{"type":"message","id":"65194b91","parentId":"8e2b576d","timestamp":"2026-05-31T17:33:52.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The expressions are ALL pure now - every number in every expression is from the 114514 universe. The problem is:\n\n1. `54 × 1` - the `× 1` is ugly. The divisor approach gives `k=1` when divisor == n.\n2. 87 = `54 × 1 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1` should just be `54 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1`\n3. Some expressions are very long (25826985564)\n\nThe `× 1` issue: this happens because `for divisor in [14514, 514, 114, 1451, 1145, 54, 51]` and when n = 54, it finds divisor 54, k = 1, r = 0... wait r = 0 so `if r != 0` should skip it. Let me check 87:\n- 87 / 14514 = 0 → skip\n- 87 / 514 = 0 → skip  \n- 87 / 114 = 0 → skip\n- 87 / 1451 = 0 → skip\n- 87 / 1145 = 0 → skip\n- 87 / 54 = 1 remainder 33 → k=1, r=33, r!=0, not has_digit_zero(33) → recurse k=1 returns \"1\", r=33 → 33/51=0... 33/54 fails... 33/51 fails... 33/14=2 rem 5 → r=5 in ALL_POOL, k=2 not in ALL_POOL... \n\nActually 87 is small (< 114514) and the divisor approach with k=1, r=33 proceeds: k_part = \"1\" (since 1 is in ALL_POOL), r_part = some decomposition of 33.\n\n33/14 = 2 rem 5 → 2 not in ALL_POOL and 5 in ALL_POOL. k=2 not in ALL_POOL and k < 114514 so goes to greedy addition: 2 = 1 + 1. So r_part = \"14 × 1 + 1 + 5\".\n\nSo 87 = 54 × 1 + 14 × 1 + 1 + 5 + ... no wait, that doesn't match.\n\nActually looking at the output: `87 = 54 × 1 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1`\n\nThis means the divisor approach for 87: divisor=54, k=1, r=33 → k_part=\"1\", and r=33 got decomposed as 15+15+1+1+1. So the result is \"54 × 1 + 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 + 1\".\n\nThe `× 1` comes from k=1. I could check if k==1 and just skip the multiplication part, returning `f\"{divisor} + {r_part}\"`.\n\nAlso for 25826985564, the output has `× 1` throughout and is very long. This is because the decomposition of large numbers eventually reaches small parts that use the divisor approach with k=1.\n\nLet me fix the `× 1` issue and see if the results are cleaner.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"有点小瑕疵——`54 × 1` 这种不该出现。修一下。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_J8dznpiegSyaH4KI4fhz9214","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# Fix: when k == 1, just use divisor + r_part instead of divisor × 1 + r_part\ncontent = content.replace(\n    'if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                    if (k in ALL_POOL or k < 114514) and (r in ALL_POOL or r < 114514):\\n                        k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                        r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                        return f\\\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"',\n    'if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                    if (k in ALL_POOL or k < 114514) and (r in ALL_POOL or r < 114514):\\n                        r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                        if k == 1:\\n                            return f\\\"{divisor} + {r_part}\\\"\\n                        k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                        return f\\\"{divisor} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"'\n)\n\n# Also fix for large number divisor fallback\ncontent = content.replace(\n    'if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                return f\\\"{name} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"',\n    'if r != 0 and not has_digit_zero(r):\\n                r_part = _recurse_stench(r, depth+1)\\n                if k == 1:\\n                    return f\\\"{name} + {r_part}\\\"\\n                k_part = _recurse_stench(k, depth+1)\\n                return f\\\"{name} × {k_part} + {r_part}\\\"'\n)\n\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/workspace-son/stench_number/generate.py', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nprint('done')\n\"\n"},"partialArgs":